<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
Description of female: 
<bibRefCitation author="Ebmer, AW" journalOrPublisher="Linzer Biologische Beitraege" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="469 - 506" refId="B35" refString="Ebmer, AW, 1980. Asiatische Halictidae (Apoidea, Hymenoptera). Linzer Biologische Beitraege 12 (2): 469 - 506" title="Asiatische Halictidae (Apoidea, Hymenoptera)." volume="12" year="1980">Ebmer 1980</bibRefCitation>
: 493, Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Halictus fulvitarsis Morawitz, 1876, holotype, female A habitus, lateral view and labels B metasoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.994.58441.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/476411" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">12</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Halictus fuscicollis Morawitz, 1876, lectotype, female A habitus, lateral view and labels B head, frontal view C mesosoma, dorsal view D metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.994.58441.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/476412" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">13</figureCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ebmer" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasioglossum melan" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melan">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Lasioglossum melan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ebmer, 1980 (synonymised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ebmer, AW" journalOrPublisher="Linzer Biologische Beitraege" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="365 - 430" refId="B43" refString="Ebmer, AW, 1998. Asiatische Halictidae - 7. Neue Lasioglossum -Arten mit einer Uebersicht der Lasioglossum s. str.-Arten der nepalischen und yunnanischen Subregion, sowie des noerdlichen Zentral-China (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Halictidae: Halictinae). Linzer Biologische Beitraege 30 (1): 365 - 430" title="Asiatische Halictidae - 7. Neue Lasioglossum - Arten mit einer Uebersicht der Lasioglossum s. str. - Arten der nepalischen und yunnanischen Subregion, sowie des noerdlichen Zentral-China (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Halictidae: Halictinae)." volume="30" year="1998">Ebmer 1998</bibRefCitation>
: 382).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
The lectotype designations by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ebmer, AW" journalOrPublisher="Linzer Biologische Beitraege" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="469 - 506" refId="B35" refString="Ebmer, AW, 1980. Asiatische Halictidae (Apoidea, Hymenoptera). Linzer Biologische Beitraege 12 (2): 469 - 506" title="Asiatische Halictidae (Apoidea, Hymenoptera)." volume="12" year="1980">Ebmer (1980</bibRefCitation>
: 495) and by 
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke, K" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Venezia" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="67 - 166" refId="B75" refString="Warncke, K, 1982. Beitrag zur Bienenfauna des Iran. 14. Die Gattung Halictus Latr., mit Bemerkungen ueber unbekannte und neue Halictus -Arten in der Westpalaearktis und Zentralasien. Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Venezia 32: 67 - 166" title="Beitrag zur Bienenfauna des Iran. 14. Die Gattung Halictus Latr., mit Bemerkungen ueber unbekannte und neue Halictus - Arten in der Westpalaearktis und Zentralasien." volume="32" year="1982">Warncke (1982</bibRefCitation>
: 91) were unnecessary as the species was described from a single male that was directly written about by 
<bibRefCitation author="Morawitz, F" journalOrPublisher="Izvestiya Imperatorskogo Obshchestva Lyubiteley Estestvoznaniya, Anthropologii i Ethnografii" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="161 - 303" refId="B52" refString="Morawitz, F, 1876. A Travel to Turkestan by the Member-Founder of the Society A.P. Fedtschenko, accomplished from the Imperial Society of Naturalists, Anthropologists, and Ethnographists on a Commission from the General-Governor of Turkestan K.P. von Kaufmann (Issue 13). Vol. II. Zoogeographical Investigations. Pt. V. (Division 7). Bees (Mellifera). Pt. II [Andrenidae]. Izvestiya Imperatorskogo Obshchestva Lyubiteley Estestvoznaniya, Anthropologii i Ethnografii 21 (3): 161 - 303" title="A Travel to Turkestan by the Member-Founder of the Society A. P. Fedtschenko, accomplished from the Imperial Society of Naturalists, Anthropologists, and Ethnographists on a Commission from the General-Governor of Turkestan K. P. von Kaufmann (Issue 13). Vol. II. Zoogeographical Investigations. Pt. V. (Division 7). Bees (Mellifera). Pt. II [Andrenidae]." volume="21" year="1876">Morawitz (1876</bibRefCitation>
: 241).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
